<REFEX REG08-TYPE="pronoun" EMPHATIC="yes" HEAD="rel-pron" CASE="nominative">who himself</REFEX>
</ALT-REFEX>
</REF>
, Baron Giddens (born January 18, 1938) is a British sociologist 
<REF ID="1432.2" SEMCAT="person" SYNCAT="np-subj">
<REFEX REG08-TYPE="pronoun" EMPHATIC="no" HEAD="rel-pron" CASE="nominative">who</REFEX>
<ALT-REFEX>
<REFEX REG08-TYPE="name" EMPHATIC="no" HEAD="nominal" CASE="plain">Anthony Giddens</REFEX>
<REFEX REG08-TYPE="name" EMPHATIC="yes" HEAD="nominal" CASE="plain">Anthony Giddens himself</REFEX>
<REFEX REG08-TYPE="name" EMPHATIC="no" HEAD="nominal" CASE="plain">Giddens</REFEX>
<REFEX REG08-TYPE="name" EMPHATIC="yes" HEAD="nominal" CASE="plain">Giddens himself</REFEX>
<REFEX REG08-TYPE="empty">_</REFEX>
<REFEX REG08-TYPE="pronoun" EMPHATIC="no" HEAD="pronoun" CASE="nominative">he</REFEX>
<REFEX REG08-TYPE="pronoun" EMPHATIC="yes" HEAD="pronoun" CASE="nominative">he himself</REFEX>
<REFEX REG08-TYPE="pronoun" EMPHATIC="no" HEAD="rel-pron" CASE="nominative">who</REFEX>
<REFEX REG08-TYPE="pronoun" EMPHATIC="yes" HEAD="rel-pron" CASE="nominative">who himself</REFEX>
</ALT-REFEX>
</REF>
 is renowned for 
<REF ID="1432.3" SEMCAT="person" SYNCAT="subj-det">
<REFEX REG08-TYPE="pronoun" EMPHATIC="no" HEAD="pronoun" CASE="genitive">his</REFEX>
<ALT-REFEX>
<REFEX REG08-TYPE="name" EMPHATIC="no" HEAD="nominal" CASE="genitive">Anthony Giddens's</REFEX>
<REFEX REG08-TYPE="name" EMPHATIC="no" HEAD="nominal" CASE="genitive">Giddens'</REFEX>
<REFEX REG08-TYPE="name" EMPHATIC="no" HEAD="nominal" CASE="genitive">Giddens's</REFEX>
<REFEX REG08-TYPE="pronoun" EMPHATIC="no" HEAD="pronoun" CASE="genitive">his</REFEX>
<REFEX REG08-TYPE="pronoun" EMPHATIC="no" HEAD="rel-pron" CASE="genitive">whose</REFEX>
</ALT-REFEX>
</REF>
 theory of structuration and 
<REF ID="1432.4" SEMCAT="person" SYNCAT="subj-det">
<REFEX REG08-TYPE="pronoun" EMPHATIC="no" HEAD="pronoun" CASE="genitive">his</REFEX>
<ALT-REFEX>
<REFEX REG08-TYPE="name" EMPHATIC="no" HEAD="nominal" CASE="genitive">Anthony Giddens's</REFEX>
<REFEX REG08-TYPE="name" EMPHATIC="no" HEAD="nominal" CASE="genitive">Giddens'</REFEX>
<REFEX REG08-TYPE="name" EMPHATIC="no" HEAD="nominal" CASE="genitive">Giddens's</REFEX>
<REFEX REG08-TYPE="pronoun" EMPHATIC="no" HEAD="pronoun" CASE="genitive">his</REFEX>
<REFEX REG08-TYPE="pronoun" EMPHATIC="no" HEAD="rel-pron" CASE="genitive">whose</REFEX>
</ALT-REFEX>
</REF>
 holistic view of modern societies. 
<REF ID="1432.5" SEMCAT="person" SYNCAT="np-subj">
<REFEX REG08-TYPE="pronoun" EMPHATIC="no" HEAD="pronoun" CASE="nominative">He</REFEX>
<ALT-REFEX>
<REFEX REG08-TYPE="name" EMPHATIC="no" HEAD="nominal" CASE="plain">Anthony Giddens</REFEX>
<REFEX REG08-TYPE="name" EMPHATIC="yes" HEAD="nominal" CASE="plain">Anthony Giddens himself</REFEX>
<REFEX REG08-TYPE="name" EMPHATIC="no" HEAD="nominal" CASE="plain">Giddens</REFEX>
<REFEX REG08-TYPE="name" EMPHATIC="yes" HEAD="nominal" CASE="plain">Giddens himself</REFEX>
<REFEX REG08-TYPE="empty">_</REFEX>
<REFEX REG08-TYPE="pronoun" EMPHATIC="no" HEAD="pronoun" CASE="nominative">he</REFEX>
<REFEX REG08-TYPE="pronoun" EMPHATIC="yes" HEAD="pronoun" CASE="nominative">he himself</REFEX>
<REFEX REG08-TYPE="pronoun" EMPHATIC="no" HEAD="rel-pron" CASE="nominative">who</REFEX>
<REFEX REG08-TYPE="pronoun" EMPHATIC="yes" HEAD="rel-pron" CASE="nominative">who himself</REFEX>
</ALT-REFEX>
</REF>
 is considered to be one of the most prominent modern contributors in the field of sociology, the author of at least 34 books, published in at least 29 languages, issuing on average more than one book every year. 
<REF ID="1432.6" SEMCAT="person" SYNCAT="np-subj">
<REFEX REG08-TYPE="pronoun" EMPHATIC="no" HEAD="pronoun" CASE="nominative">He</REFEX>
<ALT-REFEX>
<REFEX REG08-TYPE="name" EMPHATIC="no" HEAD="nominal" CASE="plain">Anthony Giddens</REFEX>
<REFEX REG08-TYPE="name" EMPHATIC="yes" HEAD="nominal" CASE="plain">Anthony Giddens himself</REFEX>
<REFEX REG08-TYPE="name" EMPHATIC="no" HEAD="nominal" CASE="plain">Giddens</REFEX>
<REFEX REG08-TYPE="name" EMPHATIC="yes" HEAD="nominal" CASE="plain">Giddens himself</REFEX>
<REFEX REG08-TYPE="empty">_</REFEX>
<REFEX REG08-TYPE="pronoun" EMPHATIC="no" HEAD="pronoun" CASE="nominative">he</REFEX>
<REFEX REG08-TYPE="pronoun" EMPHATIC="yes" HEAD="pronoun" CASE="nominative">he himself</REFEX>
<REFEX REG08-TYPE="pronoun" EMPHATIC="no" HEAD="rel-pron" CASE="nominative">who</REFEX>
<REFEX REG08-TYPE="pronoun" EMPHATIC="yes" HEAD="rel-pron" CASE="nominative">who himself</REFEX>
</ALT-REFEX>
</REF>
 has been described as Britain's best known social scientist since John Maynard Keynes.
</PARAGRAPH>

<PARAGRAPH>
Three notable stages can be identified in 
<REF ID="1432.7" SEMCAT="person" SYNCAT="subj-det">
<REFEX REG08-TYPE="pronoun" EMPHATIC="no" HEAD="pronoun" CASE="genitive">his</REFEX>
<ALT-REFEX>
<REFEX REG08-TYPE="name" EMPHATIC="no" HEAD="nominal" CASE="genitive">Anthony Giddens's</REFEX>
<REFEX REG08-TYPE="name" EMPHATIC="no" HEAD="nominal" CASE="genitive">Giddens'</REFEX>
<REFEX REG08-TYPE="name" EMPHATIC="no" HEAD="nominal" CASE="genitive">Giddens's</REFEX>
<REFEX REG08-TYPE="pronoun" EMPHATIC="no" HEAD="pronoun" CASE="genitive">his</REFEX>
<REFEX REG08-TYPE="pronoun" EMPHATIC="no" HEAD="rel-pron" CASE="genitive">whose</REFEX>
</ALT-REFEX>
</REF>
 academic life. The first one involved outlining a new vision of what sociology is, presenting a theoretical and methodological understanding of that field, based on a critical reinterpretation of the classics. 
<REF ID="1432.8" SEMCAT="person" SYNCAT="subj-det">
<REFEX REG08-TYPE="pronoun" EMPHATIC="no" HEAD="pronoun" CASE="genitive">His</REFEX>
<ALT-REFEX>
<REFEX REG08-TYPE="name" EMPHATIC="no" HEAD="nominal" CASE="genitive">Anthony Giddens's</REFEX>
<REFEX REG08-TYPE="name" EMPHATIC="no" HEAD="nominal" CASE="genitive">Giddens'</REFEX>
<REFEX REG08-TYPE="name" EMPHATIC="no" HEAD="nominal" CASE="genitive">Giddens's</REFEX>
<REFEX REG08-TYPE="pronoun" EMPHATIC="no" HEAD="pronoun" CASE="genitive">his</REFEX>
<REFEX REG08-TYPE="pronoun" EMPHATIC="no" HEAD="rel-pron" CASE="genitive">whose</REFEX>
</ALT-REFEX>
</REF>
 major publications of that era include Capitalism and Modern Social Theory (1971) and New Rules of Sociological Method (1976). In the second stage 
<REF ID="1432.9" SEMCAT="person" SYNCAT="np-subj">
<REFEX REG08-TYPE="name" EMPHATIC="no" HEAD="nominal" CASE="plain">Giddens</REFEX>
<ALT-REFEX>
<REFEX REG08-TYPE="name" EMPHATIC="no" HEAD="nominal" CASE="plain">Anthony Giddens</REFEX>
<REFEX REG08-TYPE="name" EMPHATIC="yes" HEAD="nominal" CASE="plain">Anthony Giddens himself</REFEX>
<REFEX REG08-TYPE="name" EMPHATIC="no" HEAD="nominal" CASE="plain">Giddens</REFEX>
<REFEX REG08-TYPE="name" EMPHATIC="yes" HEAD="nominal" CASE="plain">Giddens himself</REFEX>
<REFEX REG08-TYPE="empty">_</REFEX>
<REFEX REG08-TYPE="pronoun" EMPHATIC="no" HEAD="pronoun" CASE="nominative">he</REFEX>
<REFEX REG08-TYPE="pronoun" EMPHATIC="yes" HEAD="pronoun" CASE="nominative">he himself</REFEX>
<REFEX REG08-TYPE="pronoun" EMPHATIC="no" HEAD="rel-pron" CASE="nominative">who</REFEX>
<REFEX REG08-TYPE="pronoun" EMPHATIC="yes" HEAD="rel-pron" CASE="nominative">who himself</REFEX>
</ALT-REFEX>
</REF>
 developed the theory of structuration, an analysis of agency and structure, in which primacy is granted to neither. 
<REF ID="1432.10" SEMCAT="person" SYNCAT="subj-det">
<REFEX REG08-TYPE="pronoun" EMPHATIC="no" HEAD="pronoun" CASE="genitive">His</REFEX>
<ALT-REFEX>
<REFEX REG08-TYPE="name" EMPHATIC="no" HEAD="nominal" CASE="genitive">Anthony Giddens's</REFEX>
<REFEX REG08-TYPE="name" EMPHATIC="no" HEAD="nominal" CASE="genitive">Giddens'</REFEX>
<REFEX REG08-TYPE="name" EMPHATIC="no" HEAD="nominal" CASE="genitive">Giddens's</REFEX>
<REFEX REG08-TYPE="pronoun" EMPHATIC="no" HEAD="pronoun" CASE="genitive">his</REFEX>
<REFEX REG08-TYPE="pronoun" EMPHATIC="no" HEAD="rel-pron" CASE="genitive">whose</REFEX>
</ALT-REFEX>
</REF>
 works of that period, like Central Problems in Social Theory (1979) and The Constitution of Society (1984) brought 
<REF ID="1432.11" SEMCAT="person" SYNCAT="np-obj">
<REFEX REG08-TYPE="pronoun" EMPHATIC="no" HEAD="pronoun" CASE="accusative">him</REFEX>
<ALT-REFEX>
<REFEX REG08-TYPE="name" EMPHATIC="no" HEAD="nominal" CASE="plain">Anthony Giddens</REFEX>
<REFEX REG08-TYPE="name" EMPHATIC="yes" HEAD="nominal" CASE="plain">Anthony Giddens himself</REFEX>
<REFEX REG08-TYPE="name" EMPHATIC="no" HEAD="nominal" CASE="plain">Giddens</REFEX>
<REFEX REG08-TYPE="name" EMPHATIC="yes" HEAD="nominal" CASE="plain">Giddens himself</REFEX>
<REFEX REG08-TYPE="pronoun" EMPHATIC="no" HEAD="pronoun" CASE="accusative">him</REFEX>
<REFEX REG08-TYPE="pronoun" EMPHATIC="yes" HEAD="pronoun" CASE="accusative">him himself</REFEX>
<REFEX REG08-TYPE="pronoun" EMPHATIC="no" HEAD="pronoun" CASE="accusative">himself</REFEX>
</ALT-REFEX>
</REF>
 international fame on the sociological arena. The most recent stage concerns modernity, globalization and politics, especially the impact of modernity on social and personal life. This stage is reflected by 
<REF ID="1432.12" SEMCAT="person" SYNCAT="subj-det">
<REFEX REG08-TYPE="pronoun" EMPHATIC="no" HEAD="pronoun" CASE="genitive">his</REFEX>
<ALT-REFEX>
<REFEX REG08-TYPE="name" EMPHATIC="no" HEAD="nominal" CASE="genitive">Anthony Giddens's</REFEX>
<REFEX REG08-TYPE="name" EMPHATIC="no" HEAD="nominal" CASE="genitive">Giddens'</REFEX>
<REFEX REG08-TYPE="name" EMPHATIC="no" HEAD="nominal" CASE="genitive">Giddens's</REFEX>
<REFEX REG08-TYPE="pronoun" EMPHATIC="no" HEAD="pronoun" CASE="genitive">his</REFEX>
<REFEX REG08-TYPE="pronoun" EMPHATIC="no" HEAD="rel-pron" CASE="genitive">whose</REFEX>
</ALT-REFEX>
</REF>
 critique of postmodernity, and discussions of a new "utopian-realist" third way in politics, visible in the Consequence of Modernity (1990), Modernity and Self-Identity (1991), The Transformation of Intimacy (1992), Beyond Left and Right (1994) and The Third Way: The Renewal of Social Democracy (1998). 
<REF ID="1432.13" SEMCAT="person" SYNCAT="subj-det">
<REFEX REG08-TYPE="name" EMPHATIC="no" HEAD="nominal" CASE="genitive">Giddens'</REFEX>
<ALT-REFEX>
<REFEX REG08-TYPE="name" EMPHATIC="no" HEAD="nominal" CASE="genitive">Anthony Giddens's</REFEX>
<REFEX REG08-TYPE="name" EMPHATIC="no" HEAD="nominal" CASE="genitive">Giddens'</REFEX>
<REFEX REG08-TYPE="name" EMPHATIC="no" HEAD="nominal" CASE="genitive">Giddens's</REFEX>
<REFEX REG08-TYPE="pronoun" EMPHATIC="no" HEAD="pronoun" CASE="genitive">his</REFEX>
<REFEX REG08-TYPE="pronoun" EMPHATIC="no" HEAD="rel-pron" CASE="genitive">whose</REFEX>
</ALT-REFEX>
</REF>
 ambition is both to recast social theory and to re-examine our understanding of the development and trajectory of modernity. It is not clear, however, that 
<REF ID="1432.14" SEMCAT="person" SYNCAT="subj-det">
<REFEX REG08-TYPE="pronoun" EMPHATIC="no" HEAD="pronoun" CASE="genitive">his</REFEX>
<ALT-REFEX>
<REFEX REG08-TYPE="name" EMPHATIC="no" HEAD="nominal" CASE="genitive">Anthony Giddens's</REFEX>
<REFEX REG08-TYPE="name" EMPHATIC="no" HEAD="nominal" CASE="genitive">Giddens'</REFEX>
<REFEX REG08-TYPE="name" EMPHATIC="no" HEAD="nominal" CASE="genitive">Giddens's</REFEX>
<REFEX REG08-TYPE="pronoun" EMPHATIC="no" HEAD="pronoun" CASE="genitive">his</REFEX>
<REFEX REG08-TYPE="pronoun" EMPHATIC="no" HEAD="rel-pron" CASE="genitive">whose</REFEX>
</ALT-REFEX>
</REF>
 theories have had any beneficial impact on social research. 
<REF ID="1432.15" SEMCAT="person" SYNCAT="subj-det">
<REFEX REG08-TYPE="pronoun" EMPHATIC="no" HEAD="pronoun" CASE="genitive">His</REFEX>
<ALT-REFEX>
<REFEX REG08-TYPE="name" EMPHATIC="no" HEAD="nominal" CASE="genitive">Anthony Giddens's</REFEX>
<REFEX REG08-TYPE="name" EMPHATIC="no" HEAD="nominal" CASE="genitive">Giddens'</REFEX>
<REFEX REG08-TYPE="name" EMPHATIC="no" HEAD="nominal" CASE="genitive">Giddens's</REFEX>
<REFEX REG08-TYPE="pronoun" EMPHATIC="no" HEAD="pronoun" CASE="genitive">his</REFEX>
<REFEX REG08-TYPE="pronoun" EMPHATIC="no" HEAD="rel-pron" CASE="genitive">whose</REFEX>
</ALT-REFEX>
</REF>
 theories have been criticised as being empty conceptual schemes lacking any empirical implications.</PARAGRAPH>
